Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Changning Kang

2023-03-11

My meme

My meme described my state under different circumstances (studying and playing).

Here is my meme

library(magick)
# First meme
image1 <- image_read("https://tu.gtmm.net:8988/uploads/allimg/220727/4-220HG60117.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("400x400!")

# Second meme
image2 <- image_read("https://img.moegirl.org.cn/common/c/cb/Doraemon2.png") %>%
  image_resize("400x400!")

# Text 1
text1 <- image_blank(width = 400, height = 400, color = "#ffffcc") %>% # Size and color
  image_annotate(text = "It's time \nto study",  # the content of text 1
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Text 2
text2 <- image_blank(width = 400, height = 400, color = "#ffffcc") %>% # Size and color
  image_annotate(text = " It's time \nto play",  # the content of text 2
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# To build the meme
combination1 <- image_append(c(text1, image1)) # first row
combination2 <- image_append(c(image2, text2)) # second row

# To build the whole square meme
square_meme <- image_append(c(combination1, combination2), stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(600) # square meme 

#Save my meme
image_write(square_meme, "my_meme.png")
square_meme

My animation

My animation is composed by 4 memes, which blessed the four periods of the day.

Here is my animation

library(magick)
# first image
meme1 <- image_read("https://i0.wp.com/onlymyenglish.com/wp-content/uploads/new-good-morning-images.jpg?w=700&ssl=1") %>%
  image_resize("400x400!")

# second image
meme2 <- image_read("https://goodmorningland.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Good-Afternoon-My-Lovely-Friend-768x768.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("400x400!")

# third image
meme3 <- image_read("https://i0.wp.com/quoteshindi.net/wp-content/uploads/good-evening.jpg?w=700&ssl=1") %>%
  image_resize("400x400!")

# fourth image
meme4 <- image_read("https://www.wishesmsg.com/wp-content/uploads/goodnight-message.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("400x400!")

# build animation 
animation <- image_animate(c(meme1, meme2, meme3, meme4), fps = 5) # combine memes to build frame

# save my animation 
animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")

animation
